---
description: General JavaScript rules. Local tooling runs on Node.js v24; Screeps in-game code must remain compatible with the Screeps runtime.
alwaysApply: true
---
- Node.js v24 is the baseline for local tooling (scripts, CI, deploy).
- Screeps in-game code (under src/) must stay compatible with the Screeps runtime; prefer conservative syntax unless confirmed supported in-game.
- Use const for requires and module exports (CommonJS)
- Prefer const/let over var
- Use arrow functions for callbacks
- Use template literals for string interpolation
- Use destructuring when appropriate
- Use classes for controllers and behaviors
- Use JSDoc comments for all public methods with @param and @returns
- For Node-only scripts, prefer WHATWG URL APIs (URL / URLSearchParams) over deprecated url.parse()
